Manchester United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has said he is targeting “two or three” new signings in the January transfer window. The Red Devils have been linked with a number of forwards, after Romelu Lukaku and Alexis Sanchez exits in the summer. Solskjaer, speaking with BT Sport, however would not be drawn on specific players. “We’re looking to strengthen in many positions. “If you look at our squad compared to others we’re getting there. “But we need two or three players to have a squad with enough numbers to rotate throughout a long season and we’ll see what we sign,” the Norwegian said. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.